## Phase 4.2 — DM perspective read-model and rig contracts (secondary)

**Authority:** [[decisions-log]] **D-131** supersedes the **D-059** rule that DM shell **conceptual** work had to wait until after the **4.1** spine. **4.1** stays **player-first only**; **4.2** is the **sibling** home for DM design.

**Pattern backbone:** Mirror **4.1** — committed sim observables and tick commits as the **read-model** source; presentation and rigs are **query-side**; **no** mutation path from DM presentation/tooling into **`AgencySliceApplyLedger_v0`** (same CQRS discipline as **4.1**).

### Objectives (opening tranche)

- Draft **DM-specific** presentation read-models for **free-cam** and **orthographic tabletop** modes (naming, inputs vs committed state, what is replay-relevant vs UX-only per **D-027**).
- Specify **mode transition / interpolator** contract at the **presentation** boundary (aligned with master goal: smooth switches without breaking decision flow).
- Cross-link **3.4.5** / **3.4.6** DM promotion hints (**`ToolActionQueue_v0`**, **T-DM-P01–P05**) into checkable WBS-style leaves (IDs to be assigned on deepen).
- Explicit **non-claims:** literal replay columns, golden rows, and registry CI remain gated on **D-032** / **D-043** the same way as **4.1**.

### Interface table (v0 — stub)

| Artifact | Role | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `DmPresentationViewState_v0` (working name) | DM FOV / mode / tooling hooks | Split or facet **free-cam** vs **orthographic**; TBD on deepen |
| `DmCameraBinding_v0` (working name) | Rig ↔ world anchor for DM modes | Replay-relevant fields TBD with **CameraBinding_v0** parity |
| Mode transition envelope | Interpolation targets + easing profile ids | UX vs replay split per **4.1** precedent |

